Hosting Hive on cloud with the specifications below marks as a pitstop of the lab.
RAM: 8GB+ (Recommend 16 GB)
HDD: 50+ GB
OS: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS

The Hive consists of three major components:
Java - Provides the core framework for its scalable and reliable operations.
Cassandra - Primary database to store large volumes of incident data with high availability across distributed systems.
ElasticSearch - Fast indexing and search, enabling quick retrieval and correlation of cases and alerts. This also occupies majority of the space that is provided for the Hive

Upon installing the above mentioned, Hive dasboard hosted on the public IP address is all set for case management as it receives signal from the shuffle.
